data.summary#Summary:
In this code, Commands and Subsystem classes were created for each of the 3 parts of an example intake. When using the commands and values together, we can program an intake to:
Deploy to a "Floor position"
Run intake wheels to pick up a game piece
Detect the game piece with an IR sensor, causing the wrist to return into the robot's frame
Spit out the game piece by reversing the direction of the intake wheels (Into a scoring zone, stow, etc.)
